<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Viewing the meeting summary</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Click the "Meeting summary" tab</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Once the transcript is available, click the <strong>"Meeting summary"</strong> tab.
      If a summary has not been generated yet, Minute AI will use
      <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ai/generative-ai/nova/" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Amazon Nova Pro<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>
      via Amazon Bedrock to create one based on your selected template.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Review the structured minutes</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The AI generates a comprehensive set of meeting minutes organised into clear sections:
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="ndx-minutes-sections">
  <div class="ndx-minutes-section">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Meeting Overview</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Date, time, attendees, and purpose of the meeting
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-minutes-section">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Executive Summary</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      A concise summary of the meeting's key outcomes
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-minutes-section">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Discussion Points</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Major topics discussed, with context and different perspectives raised
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-minutes-section">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Key Decisions</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Decisions made during the meeting, clearly stated
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-minutes-section">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Action Items</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Tasks assigned, with responsible parties and deadlines where mentioned
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-minutes-section">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Next Steps</h4>
    <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      Follow-up actions and any agreed next meeting date
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Citations and traceability</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  A key feature of Minute AI is that the generated minutes include <strong>citations</strong>
  that link back to specific sections of the transcript. This means:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>Every claim is traceable</strong> -- you can verify what was actually said</li>
  <li><strong>Context is preserved</strong> -- click a citation to see the full discussion</li>
  <li><strong>Accuracy is verifiable</strong> -- compare the AI summary with the original words</li>
</ul>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    <strong>Try this:</strong> Click on a citation link within the minutes to jump to the
    corresponding section of the transcript. This is especially useful for verifying that
    action items and decisions have been captured accurately.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Try a different template</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  You can regenerate the minutes using a different template to see how the output changes:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Click "Generate New"</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Look for the option to generate a new summary or change the template.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Select a different template</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Try switching between "General", "Cabinet", or "Planning Committee" to see how
      each template structures the same meeting content differently.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Compare the outputs</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Notice how different templates emphasise different aspects -- a Cabinet template
      highlights motions and votes, while a General template focuses on discussion and actions.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="ndx-feature-highlight">
  <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">How Amazon Nova Pro generates minutes</h4>
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ai/generative-ai/nova/" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Amazon Nova Pro<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>
    is a foundation model available through Amazon Bedrock. It analyses the full transcript,
    understands the structure and flow of the discussion, and generates minutes that follow
    the selected template's format. The model is instructed to be accurate and to only include
    information that was actually discussed in the meeting.
  </p>
</div>

{# Troubleshooting #}
<details class="govuk-details govuk-!-margin-top-6">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
    <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
      Troubleshooting: Minutes not generating
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="govuk-details__text">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If the meeting summary does not appear:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Ensure the transcription has completed first -- check the Transcript tab</li>
      <li>Minute generation takes 1 to 3 minutes depending on transcript length</li>
      <li>Check the CloudWatch Logs for any Amazon Bedrock errors</li>
      <li>Try refreshing the page after a few minutes</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

